post_text:
Dear Haldane Community,

Today, Governor Cuomo issued an executive order postponing the School Budget Vote and Trustee Election to Tuesday, June 16, 2020. Per the executive order, Haldane Central School District will be accepting mailed absentee ballots through 5:00pm on June 16.

Ballots may be dropped off at the Haldane District Office on June 8 and June 9 between 12:00 - 5:00pm only. All other ballots must be received by mail. No additional drop off dates are permitted.

The School Budget Vote and Trustee Election Annual Meeting is anticipated to begin at 8:00pm on June 16, 2020.

Ballots were mailed to all registered voters on Friday, May 22. If you are still in need of an absentee ballot, please contact Catherine Platt, District Clerk, cplatt@haldaneschool.org

Sincerely,
Phil Benante, Ed. D.
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Just a few weeks ago, the HS Debate Team, led by Captain, Sophia Kottman, made the annual trip to Bard College to participate in a tournament with 5 other schools.
The debate topics were the most difficult to date, asking the students to challenge each other on imposing BBC impartiality standards on all news platforms, implementing a social credit system in liberal democracies, and abolishing the Olympics.

Grouped into 4 teams, the students handled themselves admirably, winning most contests. Celia Drury, Stephen Robinson, and Luca Vladimiroff finished in the top 5 teams of the day, along with the 2-person team of Aidan Hoch-Sullivan and Sophia Kottman. Individually, Stephen and Sophia finished as 2 of the top 10 debaters in the competition.

Congrats!

post_text:
It's School Board Recognition Week--

The New York State School Boards Association recognizes October 21 - 25 as School Board Recognition Week. This is a time to promote awareness and understanding of the important work performed by school board members. Haldane Central School District is joining all public school districts across the state to celebrate School Board Recognition Week to honor local board members for their commitment to the Haldane community and its children.

The Haldane Board of Education was honored at its October 15 meeting. Thank you to all Haldane school board members who work hard for our students!
Ms. Jennifer Daly, President
Mr. John Hedlund, Vice President
Dr. Peggy Clements, Trustee
Mr. Sean McNall, Trustee
Ms. Margaret Parr, Trustee

NOTICE: The Putnam County Commissioner of Finance has temporarily suspended all School tax payments due to a file control error causing Veteran Exemptions to exceed maximum limits, thereby causing 2019/20 school tax bills to be incorrect.

Corrected School Tax bills will be mailed the week of September 16, 2019.

School Tax collections will resume the week of September 16, 2019, please check with your local tax collector regarding the exact date to pay in person or online, if applicable.

The corrected school tax bill will read "CORRECTED BILL" at the top and bottom of the bill and be printed on yellow paper.

post_text:
Every morning for some time, our Food Service Director, Nancy Norton, had to use this yellow crowbar to open the frozen-closed freezer. Haldane replaced the freezer over the summer, and in recognition of Mrs. Norton's ingenuity, perseverance, and steadfast commitment to getting the job done, Dr. Benante awarded her the Golden Crowbar.

Congratulations, Mrs. Norton!

#HaldanePride
text:
Every morning for some time, our Food Service Director, Nancy Norton, had to use this yellow crowbar to open the frozen-closed freezer. Haldane replaced the freezer over the summer, and in recognition of Mrs. Norton's ingenuity, perseverance, and steadfast commitment to getting the job done, Dr. Benante awarded her the Golden Crowbar.

Congratulations, Mrs. Norton!

#HaldanePride
